Description. In general appearance a small, moderately long-legged zygopteran of medium build and typical coenagrionoid appearance. Postocular lobes of head angulated and bearing a cluster of small, robust processes posterolaterally. Caudal lamellae foliate, with distinct petiole, the central lamella considerably longer and broader than the laterals (
Fig. 2
). Coloration overall neutral brown, with darker brown mottling at the extremities, especially the antennae, legs and caudal lamellae. Body surface relatively smooth, bearing only sparse, very fine setae.

